contentrichtext.text: '''Diagoras''' may refer to: *[[Diagoras of Melos]] Atheist philosopher and poet (5th century BC) *[[Diagoras of Rhodes]] boxer, Olympian (5th century BC) *Diagoras a Greek physician quoted in [[Natural History (Pliny)|''Natural History'' of Pliny]] *[[Diagoras F.C.]] football club named after Diagoras of Rhodes *[[Rhodes International Airport, "Diagoras"]] *Mr Diagoras, a character from the British science fiction series ''Doctor Who'' who became the human part of [[Dalek Sec]], a Dalek-human hybrid {{disambig}}
